her estimates suggest that the T&C sector employs around 340,000 people in the Philippines, more than a million in Indonesia, and close to 3 million in Viet Nam, mostly female migrants from rural areas.8 The majority of these workers are women \u2013 with the proportion as high as 90 per cent in Bangladesh and Cambodia, and 87 per cent in Sri Lanka (Figure 4.3). This was partly because the pace of expansion increased employment generally and drew more people into the labour force, but also because the sector favoured part- time or piece work, circumstances in which female workers have tended to predominate. In Pakistan, for example, a country in which", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "d71f6d96-9631-44aa-8b0b-6df180e037e1": {"__data__": {"id_": "d71f6d96-9631-44aa-8b0b-6df180e037e1", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2006: Trade on Human Terms", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "31a91da8d6e79a7271096bd80b6ab04d19afa121aaed92a9911275afa5842441"}, "3": {"node_id": "0df678ac-5252-40ef-9eb1-df2fbff215e7", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development 