der and Begum 2000). Economic independence and opportunities to improve educational levels have increased their empowerment within the household (Bhattarcharya and Rahman 1999). Nevertheless, within the industry, women are still subject to gender discrimination: Wage Disparities. Even though nominal as well as real wages in the T&C sector have increased over the last 20 years, women have benefited substantially less than men. Wages have risen most for skilled workers, who are usually men. Between 1990 and 1997, the gender-related wage gap widened: Female wages fell from the equivalent of 66 per cent of male wages in 1990 to 59 per cent in 1997.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0df678ac-5252-40ef-9eb1-df2fbff215e7": {"__data__": {"id_": "0df678ac-5252-40ef-9eb1-df2fbff215e7", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2006: Trade on Human Terms", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "31a91da8d6e79a7271096bd80b6ab04d19afa121aaed92a9911275afa5842441"}, "2": {"node_id": "d71f6d96-9631-44aa-8b0b-6df180e037e1", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Program