come at the expense of the countries of Latin America, Caribbean, Africa and elsewhere. 3. Within Asian exporters, the biggest gains have been experienced by China and India. In the two markets combined (EU and US), China\u2019s share has increased from 20 per cent to 27 per cent, while that of India has gone up from around 5 per cent to over 6 per cent. The shares of Cambodia, Indonesia and Viet Nam have remained largely unchanged. 4. The initial losers, in terms of the decline in value of exports to the US and EU markets combined are Nepal, the Philippines, Thailand and Pakistan (Figure 4.4). China Even during the era of quotas, China had become the largest exporter; in 2003, it had 20 TABLE 4.6 SHARE IN VALUE IN TEXTILES AND CLOTHING (%) Country US EU 2004 2005 2004 2005 Bangladesh 2.3 2.6 5.6 5.0 Cambodia 1.7 1.9 0.7 0.6 China 17.2 24.2 23 30.7 India 4.6 5.4 6.8 7.5 Indonesia 3.0 3.3 2.6 2.2 Lao PDR - - - - Nepal 0.2 0.1 0.1 0.1 Pakistan 2.9 3.1 3.6 3.0 Philippines 2.1 2.0 0.5 0.3 Sri Lanka 1.8 1.8 1.3 1.1 Thailand 2.5 2.4 1.9 1.6 Viet Nam 3.0 2.9 1.1 1.1 Asian 12 41.3 49.7 47.2 53.2 Rest of the world 58.7 50.3 52.8 46.8 World 100.0 100.0 100.0 100.0 Source: Adhikari and Yamamoto 2006.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cc953af3-9309-4e1d-a778-d8700bc0af4b": {"__data__": {"id_": "cc953af3-9309-4e1d-a778-d8700bc0af4b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2006: Trade on Human Terms", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www