esting in training programmes in partnership with MNCs, and Indian firms are providing greater emphasis on skills like software development with appro- priate quality certification. The Vietnamese Government too is encouraging overseas train- ing institutes from Australia and India to train thousands of Vietnamese in dedicated centres across the country. Labour Standards and Regulation. Some of the negative social, cultural and occupational outcomes can be mitigated if governments focus on core labour standards, human resource management practices, and domestic labour laws. Governments and industry can also work together to combat high attrition rates, by providing more training and development and offering structured career paths. Telecommunications and Other Physical Infrastructure.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9bcdbaf7-642a-412f-8774-af821662a03f": {"__data__": {"id_": "9bcdbaf7-642a-412f-8774-af821662a03f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2006: Trade on Human Terms", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "266840a81ecb6d3a3e7eb54a9653fa1cd3431bd3c3d5fb20118a4d90f9775389"}, "2": {"node_id": "4c5f83f8-af58-4d89-b6b2-1bf0bbad85aa", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.