 quite labour-intensive; for each visitor, beds have to be made, food Figure 5.3: Tourist arrivals per 100 people, 2002 Source: Aibara and Gopalani 2005. TABLE 5.2 EMPLOYMENT IN THE TOURIST INDUSTRY Countries 2004 (Millions of people) Direct Indirect Total Direct/ Share of (%) Indirect labour force in tourism (%) East", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cc58637d-7652-446a-9017-55c6e8495b33": {"__data__": {"id_": "cc58637d-7652-446a-9017-55c6e8495b33", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2006: Trade on Human Terms", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "9fb2ac89ec58e607ec854b1c49b4c8b86b0b39f97653604aa4eef07a4c3cd7e0"}, "3": {"node_id": "d6b82a77-15f6-4d10-bd94-a009b05213b9", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2006-trade-human-terms", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "280f329c93360fe41839554068bd67cb31fa04fe80e8ffac9c40179c08e19940"}}, "hash": "ae45564c138d832c73b240065ac36bc7ed7ad88297ca47d21582a50ffaa0b717", "text": "Asia China 14.8 47.5 62.3 3.2 8.3 Korea, Republic of 0.5 1.3 1.9 2.6 8.4 South-East Asia Camb